To delete duplicate records, you can use the `DELETE ... FROM ... JOIN` syntax:

    DELETE p1 
    FROM posts p1
    INNER JOIN posts p2 
    WHERE p1.key = p2.key AND p1.created_at &gt; p2.created_at;

This will delete duplicates on `key` while retaining the record with the earlier `created_at`.

Then you can add the `UNIQUE` constraint:

    ALTER TABLE posts ADD CONSTRAINT posts_key_unique UNIQUE(key);

Or better yet, make the `key` column the primary key of the table (since the table does not seem to have a PK yet):

    ALTER TABLE posts ADD PRIMARY KEY(key);

